The Bathroom

The Bathroom somehow achieves a majestic spotlessness without appearing clinical, perhaps because its overall ambience is just a touch more ivory than pure white. Opulent roll-top baths squat proudly around the room, and the fluffiest of white towels are draped luxuriously across shining brass rails within easy reach of the fortunate bather. There is an oddly incongruous smell in here, that evokes memories of the last time you took your car to the local garage.

You can see a Bath and a mechanical man (wearing  a bathrobe).

You can go west or south.

"I really must take an oil bath", says the mechanical man. "I'm rusted almost solid! If I wind down now, I may never move again…"

The mechanical man wanders south.
