The Changing Room

The changing room, a functional space, has all it needs to fulfil its principle role in life as a gatehouse between the outer region of the lobby and the inner sanctum of the bathhouse.

Furnished only with a set of plain metal lockers and an ever vigilant attendant, perpetually on duty, it is as warm, clean and soothingly lit as any of the other of the rooms in this place. There is a doorway to the east, and a cubicle to the north.

You can see the Attendant and a keyring (to which are attached a brass key, inserted into the locker door, and a card).

You can go north, east or west.

The attendant pierces you with an icy glare. "No nudity in the changing room!" she snaps, pointing towards the cubicle with a rigid metal finger.

Shrinking beneath her withering gaze, you decide to retreat to somewhere more private.
